  1. Fit two regression models \[ \begin{cases} \begin{aligned} \text{Model 1: Sugar}_{t} &= \beta_{1} + \beta_{2}t + \beta_{3}\text{Fat}_{t} + \mathcal{W}_{t} \\ \text{Model 2: Sugar}_{t} &= \beta_{1} + \beta_{2}t + \beta_{3}t^{2} + \beta_{4}\text{Fat}_{t} + \mathcal{W}_{t} \end{aligned} \end{cases} \]
fit1 <- lm(Sugar.TS ~ TimeTS + Fat.TS) 
TimeTS2 <- TimeTS^2
fit2 <- lm(Sugar.TS ~ TimeTS + TimeTS2 + Fat.TS)
